## ðŸ’» **Arduino Code: UI for Monitoring & Control**

```cpp
// CPS User Interface - Temperature Monitor & LED Control

const int sensorPin = A0;  // TMP36 pin
const int ledPin = 13;     // LED control pin

float temperatureC;
String userInput = "";

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(9600);
  pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);
  Serial.println("=== Cyber Physical System Interface ===");
  Serial.println("Commands: ");
  Serial.println("  ON  -> Turn LED ON");
  Serial.println("  OFF -> Turn LED OFF");
  Serial.println("---------------------------------------");
}

void loop() {
  // --- Read and display sensor data ---
  int reading = analogRead(sensorPin);
  float voltage = reading * (5.0 / 1023.0);
  temperatureC = (voltage - 0.5) * 100.0;

  Serial.print("Temperature: ");
  Serial.print(temperatureC);
  Serial.println(" Â°C");

  // --- User Control through Serial Monitor ---
  if (Serial.available() > 0) {
    userInput = Serial.readStringUntil('\n');
    userInput.trim();

    if (userInput == "ON" || userInput == "on") {
      digitalWrite(ledPin, HIGH);
      Serial.println("LED Turned ON âœ…");
    } 
    else if (userInput == "OFF" || userInput == "off") {
      digitalWrite(ledPin, LOW);
      Serial.println("LED Turned OFF âŒ");
    } 
    else {
      Serial.println("Invalid Command. Type 'ON' or 'OFF'.");
    }
  }

  delay(2000);
}
```

---

## ðŸ–¥ï¸ **How It Works**

1. Upload the program to Arduino.
2. Open the **Serial Monitor** (Ctrl + Shift + M).
3. Set **baud rate = 9600**.
4. Youâ€™ll see:

   ```
   === Cyber Physical System Interface ===
   Commands:
     ON  -> Turn LED ON
     OFF -> Turn LED OFF
   ---------------------------------------
   Temperature: 27.5 Â°C
   ```
5. Type `ON` â†’ LED turns ON
6. Type `OFF` â†’ LED turns OFF
